(What it is) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
0 -16 Td
(Alleato-Procore is the internal repository powering the Alleato Project Manager add-on for Procore, combining a Next.js 15 front end with a FastAPI RAG backend, Supabase schema management, and automation/docs to keep collaborators aligned.) Tj
0 -18 Td
/F1 14 Tf
(Who it is for) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
0 -16 Td
(Alleato project operations and engineering teams building and validating AI-enhanced workflows inside Procore, particularly product owners and PMs who rely on the Alleato add-on.) Tj
0 -20 Td
/F1 14 Tf
(What it does) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
0 -16 Td
(- Hosts a Next.js 15 App Router UI with domain components and Supabase queries.) Tj
0 -16 Td
(- Runs a FastAPI backend that wires ChatKit streaming and alleato_agent_workflow into a Supabase-backed RAG API.) Tj
0 -16 Td
(- Manages Supabase migrations/seeds via the supabase/ directory plus Drizzle scripts.) Tj
0 -16 Td
(- Ships Playwright and Jest automation, screenshot reports, and QA scripts.) Tj
0 -16 Td
(- Keeps docs/, docs-ai/, and PRPs/ aligned with Procore workflows.) Tj
0 -16 Td
(- Provides scripts for database seeding, crawls, and regression automation.) Tj
0 -16 Td
/F1 14 Tf
(How it works) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
0 -20 Td
(- The Next.js frontend calls FastAPI endpoints \(including /chatkit\) with CORS so the UI can reach AI-assisted flows.) Tj
0 -16 Td
(- FastAPI loads env vars, mounts SupabaseRagStore, and runs RagChatKit streaming servers tied to alleato_agent_workflow specialists.) Tj
0 -16 Td
(- Supabase holds schema, RLS policies, and data; Drizzle plus SQL migrations keep it synchronized with the app.) Tj
0 -16 Td
(- Playwright \(frontend and repo tests\) plus Jest/Allure guard UI behavior while scripts/ orchestrate seeds, crawls, and automation outputs.) Tj
0 -16 Td
(- docs/, docs-ai/, PRPs/, and screenshots/ document every workflow and verification artifact for contributors.) Tj
0 -16 Td
/F1 14 Tf
(How to run) Tj
/F1 12 Tf
0 -20 Td
(- Install Node.js 18+, npm \(pnpm supported\), Python 3.11+, Supabase creds, and an OpenAI API key per the env templates.) Tj
0 -16 Td
(- Run npm run install:all from the repo root to install root and frontend dependencies.) Tj
0 -16 Td
(- Copy templates: cp frontend/.env.example frontend/.env.local and cp backend/.env.template backend/.env, then fill Supabase/OpenAI values.) Tj
0 -16 Td
(- Start both services with npm run dev \(or run npm run dev:frontend and npm run dev:backend separately as needed\).) Tj
0 -16 Td
